VARIANCE
Variance (σ2) is the average of the squared differences from the mean.
Example: What is the variance of the data set (1,4,5,4,8)?
First, find the mean (1+4+5+4+8)/5 = 4.4
Then find the differences from the mean: (-3.4, -0.4, 0.6, -0.4, 3.6)
Find the sqared difference: (11.56, 0.16, 0.36, 0.16, 12.96)
Find the average of the squared differences: 
